label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v6

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of maxillary sinus cancer, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v6 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

value.value: Maxillary sinus cancer with no distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pM1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Maxillary sinus cancer with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pMX TNM Finding v6

value.value: Maxillary sinus cancer in which distant metastasis cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 6th Ed.)

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pN0 TNM Finding v6 and v7

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pN1 TNM Finding v6 and v7

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pN2a TNM Finding v6 and v7

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pN2b TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Maxillary sinus cancer with metastasis in multiple ipsilateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pN2c TNM Finding v6 and v7

value.value: Maxillary sinus cancer with metastasis in bilateral or contralateral lymph nodes, none more than 6 cm in greatest dimension. (from AJCC 6th and 7th Eds.)

A rare benign adipose tissue neoplasm characterized by nests and cord of abundant univacuolated and multivacuolated lipoblasts and mature adipocytes in a prominent myxoid to hyalinized chondroid matrix admix. It predominantly affects females.

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pN3 TNM Finding v6 and v7

label.value: Maxillary Sinus Cancer pNX TNM Finding v6 and v7
